The paper deals with the design of parameterized algorithms for two problems in graph theory, namely List Digraph Homomorphism and Min-Max Multiway Cut. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves the use of combinatorial techniques and graph theory, which suggests that it could also be classified under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of the time complexity of the algorithms, which could also place it under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
